Infrastructure-Specific Examples
Fibonacci Sequence
Using the Fibonacci sequence for infrastructure tasks:

1 point:
Reboot a server
Apply a small configuration change
2 points:
Deploy a virtual machine from a template
Perform a minor network configuration change (e.g., update a DNS entry)
3 points:
Set up monitoring for a new service
Configure a new VLAN
5 points:
Migrate a small set of VMs to a new host
Install and configure a new storage array
8 points:
Implement a backup solution for a new environment
Upgrade the firmware on multiple network devices
13 points:
Design and implement a new disaster recovery strategy
Set up a new data center location
20 points:
Complete data center migration
Major network redesign affecting multiple sites
